<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=10013962791343></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f10013962791343><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=14&mid=10013962791343>Erudites</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=14&mid=10013962791343#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Sep 25th 1:37 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hello there.<br><br>Are you an erudite necromancer? Having trouble breaking that level 8 spot? Nothing in Paineel is any good. Warrens...woot woot...TRAIN!...and pretty much every where else? Necromancers like you GET ON MY NERVES!!! PREPARE TO DIE INFIDEL! (or something to that effect)<br><br>Well, here is the best stratedgy that I have found...<br><br>1: Start out by zoning to toxxulia forest<br><br>2: See those two skeletons regarding you indifferently? See your "Ward Undead Spell?"<br><br>3: DO NOT attack these skeletons right away. Chances are that half way through the battle the abandoned heretic pet is going to come up behind you and take you and your pet out.<br><br>4: Step out side, and look at the entrance. To the right you will see a tree. To the right of the tree is the spot where the abandoned heretic pet will come after yelling at the skeletons.<br><br>5: Cast your "Ward undead" spell on the a.h.p. If your Evocation skill is low, you can just cast ward undead on your pet. It won't hurt him! (Thanks Wtzupcom)<br><br>6: After killing the a.h.p. med up<br><br>7: Go into the cave and ward undead the skele on the left. (He's stronger) Have your pet guarding outside. Sitting so he doesn't wander off.<br><br>8: Proceed to murder the skeletons. Remember to tank for your pet a bit...he can't take two pick=axes for too long =)<br><br>9: You can repeat this until about level 12. Just easy xp and lots of bone chips.<br><br>10: All three should begin to spawn at different times making it much easier on you...<br><br><br><br>O.K. So now you're level 12...<br><br>1: GO TO KERRA ISLE!!!<br><br>2: I know that no one ever goes there, but you're not going to get trained on going there! You know you most likely will be taking 2 kerrans at once...tops!<br><br>3: First cast your dot (Heat Blood) on the right awrat. (engulfing darkness makes that one run slower, and you're going to want to get it further into the tunnel.<br><br>4: Cast Vampiric Embrace and Dark Pact before the battlel...<br><br>5: Continue killing these guys til you think you can move on to the mulmuks in the back...after you've got these guys pretty well handled...there are two more to the sides...These guys will come one at a time (Some times they bring friends.)<br><br>6: Always try and get the cats not to run outside...they'll always run to a friend.<br><br>7: Continue to til level 16. Further on if you want, but...I hear that can get irritating...<br><br><br>I've also heard that you can fight sirens...but I personally have no idea where you can find them.<br><br><br>-Kruwl<br>-Level 15 Necromancer (Erudite)<br>-master at /gems<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
