<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100210532254667></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100210532254667><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=14&mid=100210532254667>RE: i hear things</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=14&mid=100210532254667#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=49677><span id=Sage>alaaraaf</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>111 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Oct 3rd 6:35 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Another answer that's probably too late...<br><br>Research is a pain in the ass.  The main reason for this, is that the words you want for a spell of level x typically drop from monsters of level x+1 to level x+4.  This means that unless you are always in good groups, you will always take a coupla levels to get the right words.<br><br>Another pain in the ass, is that if you're trying to make the spell, there's a goodly chance you're gonna fail.  Believe me, there's absolutely nothing worse than failing a research, when you have no spare words and you desparately want a spell.<br><br>But, there is an up-side to all this.  Spells are not NO DROP.  So, you can either buy a complete spell from another player, or if you have the words you can ask them to research the spell for you.  (You might be charged some minimal coin for this, but my experience of it has been that EVERY time I have asked someone to do this, they have done so for free!)<br><br>Buying spells can be somewhat costly, but, by the time you're needing a spell, the cost should be well within your grasp.  (The only time this has not been true in my experience, were the low level spells.  I simply couldn't make enough coins to buy from the damned vendors.)<br><br>A thing to consider with research, is that you can train it more or less indefinitely at your guild.  (Assuming you don't mind pouring all your skill points into it...)  At L16, you can only train 1 point of skill.  But at every level thereafter, you can train another 5.  (I didn't know this and this resulted in a huge loss of spell components.  *Sigh*)<br><br>Hope this helps, at least a little.<br><br>Al-Aaraaf.<br>"Death is coming..."<br>&nbsp;<br>"Te aurdire no possum. Musa sapienum fixa est in aura."</td></tr>
